<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,582,1130]" pageId="36" pageNumber="237">
Diagnosis. Glp-1 not found. Ds-2 on membranous cuticle. PE with 1 dorsal seta. GA bipartite in female, fully sclerotized plate and separated membranous disc in male. Female with 6 Pgs and 6 Sgs. Male with 29–39 Pgs and 6 Sgs. Tr I–IV with 1-1-1-1 setae; Bf I–IV with 2-2-1-1 setae; Tf I–IV with 4-4-3-3 setae, 2-1-0-0 Bp setae; Gn I–IV with 4-5-3-3 setae, 2-1-0-0 Bp setae; Tb I–IV with 9-7-7-7 setae, 6-4-4-4 Bp setae; Ta I–IV with 3-3-3-3 dorsal setae, 1-0-0-0 Bp setae. Lc I with unidentate accessory process. 
